    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-01-06T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-01-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="657" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d657">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Following the proclamation of the Unitary State on August 17, the Hatta
                    Government remained as caretaker while President Sukarno consulted with various
                    Indonesian political leaders concerning the formation of the first Unitary State
                    Cabinet. On August 22, President Sukarno instructed Mohammad Natsir to form a
                    new government and <pb facs="1079" n="1065" xml:id="pg_1065"/> the leader of the
                        <gloss target="#t_Masjumi1">Masjumi</gloss> Party announced his Cabinet on
                    September 6, including the following officials: <table cols="2" rows="10">
                        <row>
                            <cell>Prime Minister</cell>
                            <cell>Mohammad Natsir</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Deputy Prime Minister</cell>
                            <cell>Hamengku Buwono IX (Jogja Sultan)</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Internal Affairs</cell>
                            <cell>Assaat</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Foreign Affairs</cell>
                            <cell>Mohammad Roem</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Defense</cell>
                            <cell>Abdul Halim (resigned due to poor health on December 8; duties
                                assumed by Natsir and Hamengku Buwono IX)</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Trade and Industry</cell>
                            <cell>Sumitro Djojohadikusumo</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Communications and Transport</cell>
                            <cell>Djuanda</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Health</cell>
                            <cell>Johannes Leimena</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Finance</cell>
                            <cell>Siafruddin Prawiranegrara</cell>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <cell>Information</cell>
                            <cell>M. A. Peelaupessy</cell>
                        </row>
                    </table>
                </p>
            </div>
